The paper deals with steganalysis of VoIP streams, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of attention mechanisms for correlation feature extraction suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of compressed VoIP streams, indicating a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SD) sub-categories.
